      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COMPTON LAYLA (2) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 0.8 lengths at this track in a handy 18.00 beating Cantara Pearl. Has good early burn and is drawn to be prominent. Well placed and can measure up. DUKE CABOOM (6) is a patchy beginner. Last start finished 4th over 305m at this track beaten 6 lengths (18.20) behind Rough Girl Ruby in a Other on June 18. With even luck and a clean start should be around the money. CLOSE SHAVE (4) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fifth wasn't far away finishing 3 lengths from the winner (18.21). Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. CADILLAC LANDAU (8) with some luck can improve on an unplaced run last time here.",
